item.name: MySQL Aborted clients
item.description: Number of aborted client connections. This can be due to the client not calling mysql_close() before exiting, the client sleeping without issuing a request to the server for more seconds than specified by wait_timeout or interactive_timeout, or by the client program ending in the midst of transferring data.

item.name: MySQL Aborted connects
item.description: Number of failed server connection attempts. This can be due to a client using an incorrect password, a client not having privileges to connect to a database, a connection packet not containing the correct information, or if it takes more than connect_timeout seconds to get a connect packet.

item.name: MySQL Access denied errors
item.description: Number of access denied errors.

item.name: MySQL Admin commands
item.description: Number of admin commands executed. These include table dumps, change users, binary log dumps, shutdowns, pings and debugs.

item.name: MySQL Alter Database commands
item.description: Number of ALTER DATABASE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Alter Database Upgrade commands
item.description: Number of ALTER DATABASE ... UPGRADE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Alter Event commands
item.description: Number of ALTER EVENT commands executed.

item.description: Number of ALTER PROCEDURE commands executed.

item.description: Number of ALTER SERVER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Alter Table commands
item.description: Number of ALTER TABLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Alter Tablespace commands
item.description: Number of ALTER TABLESPACE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Analyze commands
item.description: Number of ANALYZE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Assign to Key Cache commands
item.description: Number of assign to keycache commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Begin commands
item.description: Number of BEGIN statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Binlog commands
item.description: Number of BINLOG commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Busy time
item.description: Cumulative time in seconds of activity on connections.

item.name: MySQL Bytes received
item.description: Total bytes received from all clients.

item.name: MySQL Bytes sent
item.description: Total bytes sent to all clients.

item.name: MySQL Call procedure commands
item.description: Number of CALL procedure_name statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Change DB commands
item.description: Number of USE database_name commands executed.

item.name: MySQL check
item.description: Single item to trigger all checks. Get this item will launch python script on MySQL server. The script will gather all metrics we need and send them as Zabbic Trappers

item.name: MySQL Checksum commands
item.description: Number of CHECKSUM TABLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Check Table commands
item.description: Number of CHECK TABLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Commit commands
item.description: Number of COMMIT commands executed. Differs from Handler_commit, which counts internal commit statements.

item.name: MySQL Compression
item.description: Whether client-server traffic is compressed.

item.name: MySQL Connection Error Accept
item.description: Number of errors that occurred during calls to accept() on the listening port.

item.name: MySQL Connection Error Internal
item.description: Number of refused connections due to internal server errors, for example out of memory errors, or failed thread starts.

item.name: MySQL Connection Error Max Connection
item.description: Number of refused connections due to the max_connections limit being reached.

item.name: MySQL Connection Error Peer Address
item.description: Number of errors while searching for the connecting client IP address.

item.name: MySQL Connection Error Select
item.description: Number of errors during calls to select() or poll() on the listening port. The client would not necessarily have been rejected in these cases.

item.name: MySQL Connection Error TCPWrap
item.description: Number of connections the libwrap library refused.

item.name: MySQL Connections
item.description: Number of connection attempts (both successful and unsuccessful)

item.name: MySQL CPU Time
item.description: Total CPU time used.

item.name: MySQL Create DB commands
item.description: Number of CREATE DATABASE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create Event commands
item.description: Number of CREATE EVENT commands executed. Differs from Executed_events in that it is incremented when the CREATE EVENT is run, and not when the event executes.

item.name: MySQL Create Function commands
item.description: Number of CREATE FUNCTION commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create Index commands
item.description: Number of CREATE INDEX commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create Procedure commands
item.description: Number of CREATE PROCEDURE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create Role commands
item.description: Number of CREATE ROLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create Server commands
item.description: Number of CREATE SERVER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create Table commands
item.description: Number of CREATE TABLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create Trigger commands
item.description: Number of CREATE TRIGGER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create UDF commands
item.description: Number of CREATE UDF commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create User commands
item.description: Number of CREATE USER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Create View commands
item.description: Number of CREATE VIEW commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Deallocate commands
item.description: Number of DEALLOCATE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Delayed Errors
item.description: Number of errors which occurred while doing INSERT DELAYED.

item.name: MySQL Delayed Inserts Threads
item.description: Number of INSERT DELAYED threads.

item.name: MySQL Delayed Writes
item.description: Number of INSERT DELAYED rows written.

item.name: MySQL Delete commands
item.description: Number of DELETE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Do commands
item.description: Number of DO commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Database commands
item.description: Number of DROP DATABASE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Event commands
item.description: Number of DROP EVENT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Function commands
item.description: Number of DROP FUNCTION commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Index commands
item.description: Number of DROP INDEX commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Procedure commands
item.description: Number of DROP PROCEDURE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Role commands
item.description: Number of DROP ROLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Server commands
item.description: Number of DROP SERVER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Table commands
item.description: Number of DROP TABLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop Trigger commands
item.description: Number of DROP TRIGGER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop User commands
item.description: Number of DROP USER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Drop View commands
item.description: Number of DROP VIEW commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Empty Query
item.description: Number of queries to the server that do not produce SQL queries. An SQL query simply returning no results does not increment Com_empty_query - see Empty_queries instead. An example of an empty query sent to the server is mysql --comments -e '-- sql comment'

item.name: MySQL Empty Results
item.description: Number of queries returning no results. Note this is not the same as Com_empty_query.

item.name: MySQL Events
item.description: Number of times events created with CREATE EVENT have executed. This differs from Com_create_event in that it is only incremented when the event has run, not when it executes.

item.name: MySQL Execute commands
item.description: Number of EXECUTE statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Feature Dynamic columns
item.description: Number of times the COLUMN_CREATE() function was used.

item.name: MySQL Feature Full text
item.description: Number of times the MATCH … AGAINST() function was used.

item.name: MySQL Feature GIS
item.description: Number of times a table with a any of the geometry columns was opened.

item.name: MySQL Feature Locale
item.description: Number of times the @@lc_messages variable was assigned into.

item.name: MySQL Feature SubQuery
item.description: Number of subqueries (excluding subqueries in the FROM clause) used.

item.name: MySQL Feature TimeZone
item.description: Number of times an explicit timezone (excluding UTC and SYSTEM) was specified.

item.name: MySQL Feature Trigger
item.description: Number of triggers loaded.

item.name: MySQL Feature XML
item.description: Number of times XML functions (EXTRACTVALUE() and UPDATEXML()) were used.

item.name: MySQL Flush commands
item.description: Number of FLUSH statements executed. This differs from Flush_commands, which also counts internal server flush requests.

item.name: MySQL Get Diagnostics commands
item.description: Number of GET DIAGNOSTICS commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Global Flush commands
item.description: Number of FLUSH statements executed, as well as due to internal server flush requests. This differs from Com_flush, which simply counts FLUSH statements, not internal server flush operations.

item.name: MySQL Grant commands
item.description: Number of GRANT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Grant Role commands
item.description: Number of GRANT ROLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Handler Close commands
item.description: Number of HANDLER table_name CLOSE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Handler commit
item.description: Number of internal COMMIT requests. Differs from Com_commit, which counts the number of COMMIT statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Handler delete
item.description: Number of times rows have been deleted from tables. Differs from Com_delete, which counts DELETE statements.

item.name: MySQL Handler discover
item.description: Discovery is when the server asks the NDBCLUSTER storage engine if it knows about a table with a given name. Handler_discover indicates the number of times that tables have been discovered in this way.

item.name: MySQL Handler external lock
item.description: Incremented for each call to the external_lock() function, which generally occurs at the beginning and end of access to a table instance.

item.name: MySQL Handler ICP attempts
item.description: Number of times pushed index condition was checked. The smaller the ratio of Handler_icp_attempts to Handler_icp_match the better the filtering. See Index Condition Pushdown.

item.name: MySQL Handler ICP match
item.description: Number of times pushed index condition was matched. The smaller the ratio of Handler_icp_attempts to Handler_icp_match the better the filtering. See See Index Condition Pushdown.

item.name: MySQL Handler MRR init
item.description: Counts how many MRR (multi-range read) scans were performed. See Multi Range Read optimization.

item.name: MySQL Handler MRR key refills
item.description: Number of times key buffer was refilled (not counting the initial fill). A non-zero value indicates there wasn't enough memory to do key sort-and-sweep passes in one go. See Multi Range Read optimization.

item.name: MySQL Handler MRR rowid refills
item.description: Number of times rowid buffer was refilled (not counting the initial fill). A non-zero value indicates there wasn't enough memory to do rowid sort-and-sweep passes in one go. See Multi Range Read optimization.

item.name: MySQL Handler Open commands
item.description: Number of HANDLER table_name OPEN commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Handler prepare
item.description: Number of two-phase commit prepares.

item.name: MySQL Handler Read commands
item.description: Number of HANDLER table_name READ commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Handler read first
item.description: Number of requests to read the first row from an index. A high value indicates many full index scans, e.g. SELECT a FROM table_name where a is an indexed column.

item.name: MySQL Handler read key
item.description: Number of row read requests based on an index value. A high value indicates indexes are regularly being used, which is usually positive.

item.name: MySQL Handler read last
item.description: Number of requests to read the last row from an index. ORDER BY DESC results in a last-key request followed by several previous-key requests.

item.name: MySQL Handler read next
item.description: Number of requests to read the next row from an index (in order). Increments when doing an index scan or querying an index column with a range constraint.

item.name: MySQL Handler read prev
item.description: Number of requests to read the previous row from an index (in order). Mostly used with ORDER BY DESC.

item.name: MySQL Handler read rnd
item.description: Number of requests to read a row based on its position. If this value is high, you may not be using joins that don't use indexes properly, or be doing many full table scans.

item.name: MySQL Handler read rnd deleted
item.description: Number of requests to delete a row based on its position.

item.name: MySQL Handler read rnd next
item.description: Number of requests to read the next row. A large number of these may indicate many table scans and improperly used indexes.

item.name: MySQL Handler rollback
item.description: Number of transaction rollback requests given to a storage engine. Differs from Com_rollback, which is the number of ROLLBACK commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Handler savepoint
item.description: Number of transaction savepoint creation requests. Differs from Com_savepoint which is the number of SAVEPOINT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Handler savepoint rollback
item.description: Number of requests to rollback to a transaction savepoint.

item.name: MySQL Handler tmp update
item.description: Number of requests to update a row to a temporary table.

item.name: MySQL Handler tmp write
item.description: Number of requests to write a row to a temporary table.

item.name: MySQL Handler update
item.description: Number of requests to update a row in a table. Since MariaDB 5.3, this no longer counts temporary tables - see Handler_tmp_update.

item.name: MySQL Handler write
item.description: Number of requests to write a row to a table. Since MariaDB 5.3, this no longer counts temporary tables - see Handler_tmp_write.

item.name: MySQL Help commands
item.description: Number of HELP commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Immediate table locks
item.description: Number of table locks which were completed immediately.

item.name: MySQL Insert commands
item.description: Number of INSERT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Insert Select commands
item.description: Number of INSERT ... SELECT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Install Plugin commands
item.description: Number of INSTALL PLUGIN commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Key blocks not flushed
item.description: Number of key cache blocks which have been modified but not flushed to disk.

item.name: MySQL Key blocks not used
item.description: Number of unused key cache blocks.

item.name: MySQL Key blocks used
item.description: Max number of key cache blocks which have been used simultaneously.

item.name: MySQL Key blocks warm
item.description: Number of key cache blocks in the warm list.

item.name: MySQL Key read requests
item.description: Number of key cache block read requests. See Optimizing key_buffer_size.

item.name: MySQL Key reads
item.description: Number of physical index block reads. See Optimizing key_buffer_size.

item.name: MySQL Key write requests
item.description: Number of requests to write a block to the key cache.

item.name: MySQL Key writes
item.description: Number of key cache block write requests

item.name: MySQL Kill commands
item.description: Number of KILL commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Last query cost
item.description: The most recent query optimizer query cost calculation. Can not be calculated for complex queries, such as subqueries or UNION. It will be set to 0 for complex queries.

item.name: MySQL Load commands
item.description: Number of LOAD commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Lock Tables commands
item.description: Number of [lock-tables|LOCK TABLES] commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Max used connection
item.description: Max number of connections ever open at the same time.

item.name: MySQL Memory usage
item.description: Global or per-connection memory usage.

item.name: MySQL multi-table Delete commands
item.description: Number of multi-table DELETE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL multi-tables Update commands
item.description: Number of multi-tables UPDATE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Not flushed delayed rows
item.description: Number of INSERT DELAYED rows waiting to be written.

item.name: MySQL Opened files
item.description: Number of files the server has opened.

item.name: MySQL Opened table definitions
item.description: Number of .frm files that have been cached.

item.name: MySQL Opened tables
item.description: Number of tables the server has opened.

item.name: MySQL Opened views
item.description: Number of views the server has opened.

item.name: MySQL Open files
item.description: Number of regular files currently opened by the server. Does not include sockets or pipes, or storage engines using internal functions.

item.name: MySQL Open streams
item.description: Number of currently opened streams, usually log files.

item.name: MySQL Open table definitions
item.description: Number of currently cached .frm files.

item.name: MySQL Open tables
item.description: Number of currently opened tables, excluding temporary tables.

item.name: MySQL Optimize commands
item.description: Number of OPTIMIZE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL plugin discovery
item.description: Single item to trigger discovery. Getting this item will launch python script on MySQL server. The script will discover all relevant metrics and send them as Low Level Discovery

item.name: MySQL plugin Server Audit is active
MySQL Prepared statements count
item.description: Current number of prepared statements.

item.name: MySQL Prepare SQL commands
item.description: Number of PREPARE statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Purge Before commands
item.description: Number of PURGE BEFORE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Purge commands
item.description: Number of PURGE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL QCache free blocks
item.description: Number of free query cache memory blocks.

item.name: MySQL QCache free memory
item.description: Amount of free query cache memory.

item.name: MySQL QCache hits
item.description: Number of requests served by the query cache.

item.name: MySQL QCache in cache queries
item.description: Number of queries that are uncacheable by the query cache, or use SQL_NO_CACHE.

item.name: MySQL QCache inserts
item.description: Number of queries ever cached in the query cache.

item.name: MySQL QCache lowmem prunes
item.description: Number of pruning operations performed to remove old results to make space for new results in the query cache.

item.name: MySQL QCache not cached queries
item.description: Number of queries that are uncacheable by the query cache, or use SQL_NO_CACHE.

item.name: MySQL QCache total blocks
item.description: Number of queries currently cached by the query cache.

item.name: MySQL Queries
item.description: Number of statements executed by the server, excluding COM_PING and COM_STATISTICS. Differs from Questions in that it also counts statements executed within stored programs.

item.name: MySQL Questions
item.description: Number of statements executed by the server, excluding COM_PING, COM_STATISTICS, COM_STMT_PREPARE, COM_STMT_CLOSE, and COM_STMT_RESET statements. Differs from Queries in that it doesn't count statements executed within stored programs.

item.name: MySQL Release Savepoint commands
item.description: Number of RELEASE SAVEPOINT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Rename Table commands
item.description: Number of RENAME TABLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Rename User commands
item.description: Number of RENAME USER commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Repare commands
item.description: Number of REPAIR TABLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Replace commands
item.description: Number of REPLACE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Replace Select commands
item.description: Number of REPLACE ... SELECT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Reset commands
item.description: Number of RESET commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Resignal commands
item.description: Number of RESIGNAL commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Revoke All commands
item.description: Number of REVOKE ALL commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Revoke commands
item.description: Number of REVOKE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Revoke Role commands
item.description: Number of REVOKE ROLE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Rollback commands
item.description: Number of ROLLBACK commands executed. Differs from Handler_rollback, which is the number of transaction rollback requests given to a storage engine.

item.name: MySQL Rollback to Savepoint commands
item.description: Number of ROLLBACK ... TO SAVEPOINT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Rows read
item.description: Number of requests to read a row (excluding temporary tables).

item.name: MySQL Rows tmp read
item.description: Number of requests to read a row in a temporary table.

item.name: MySQL Savepoint commands
item.description: Number of SAVEPOINT commands executed. Differs from Handler_savepoint, which is the number of transaction savepoint creation requests.

item.name: MySQL Select commands
item.description: Number of SELECT commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Select full join
item.description: Number of joins which did not use an index. If not zero, you may need to check table indexes.

item.name: MySQL Select full range join
item.description: Number of joins which used a range search of the first table.

item.name: MySQL Select range
item.description: Number of joins which used a range on the first table.

item.name: MySQL Select range check
item.description: Number of joins without keys that check for key usage after each row. If not zero, you may need to check table indexes.

item.name: MySQL Select scan
item.description: Number of joins which used a full scan of the first table.

item.name: MySQL Set Option commands
item.description: Number of SET OPTION commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Show Authors commands
item.description: Number of SHOW AUTHORS commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Show Binlog Events commands
item.description: Number of SHOW BINLOG EVENTS statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Show Binlogs commands
item.description: Number of SHOW BINLOGS statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Show Charsets commands
item.description: Number of SHOW CHARSETS statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Shutdown commands
item.description: Number of SHUTDOWN commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Signal commands
item.description: Number of SIGNAL commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Slow launch threads
item.description: Number of threads which took longer than slow_launch_time to create.

item.name: MySQL Slow queries
item.description: Number of queries which took longer than long_query_time to run. The slow query log does not need to be active for this to be recorded.

item.name: MySQL Sort merge passes
item.description: Number of merge passes performed by the sort algorithm. If too high, you may need to look at improving your query indexes, or increasing the sort_buffer_size.

item.name: MySQL Sort priority queue sorts
item.description: The number of times that sorting was done through a priority queue. (The total number of times sorting was done is a sum Sort_range and Sort_scan). See filesort with small LIMIT optimization.

item.name: MySQL Sort range
item.description: Number of sorts which used a range.

item.name: MySQL Sort rows
item.description: Number of rows sorted.

item.name: MySQL Sort scan
item.description: Number of sorts which used a full table scan.

item.name: MySQL Statements close
item.description: Number of prepared statements closed (deallocated or dropped).

item.name: MySQL Statements execute
item.description: Number of prepared statements executed.

item.name: MySQL Statements fetch
item.description: Number of prepared statements fetched.

item.name: MySQL Statements long data send
item.description: Number of prepared statements where the parameter data has been sent in chunks (long data).

item.name: MySQL Statements prepare
item.description: Number of prepared statements prepared.

item.name: MySQL Statements reprepare
item.description: Number of prepared statements reprepared.

item.name: MySQL Statements reset
item.description: Number of prepared statements where the data of a prepared statement which was accumulated in chunks by sending long data has been reset.

item.name: MySQL Subquery cache hit
item.description: Counter for all subquery cache hits

item.name: MySQL Subquery cache miss
item.description: Counter for all subquery cache misses

item.name: MySQL Syncs
item.description: Number of times my_sync() has been called, or the number of times the server has had to force data to disk. Covers the binary log, .frm creation (if these operations are configured to sync) and some storage engines (Archive, CSV, Aria), but not XtraDB/InnoDB).

item.name: MySQL TC log max pages
item.description: Max number of pages used by the transaction coordinator recovery log.

item.name: MySQL TC log page size
item.description: Page size of the transaction coordinator recovery log.

item.name: MySQL TC log page waits
item.description: Number of times a two-phase commit was forced to wait for a free transaction coordinator recovery log page.

item.name: MySQL Temp Tables
item.description: Number of temporary tables created.

item.name: MySQL Temp Tables in Memory
item.description: Number of in-memory temporary tables created.

item.name: MySQL Temp Tables on disk
item.description: Number of on-disk temporary tables created.

item.name: MySQL ThreadPool cached threads
item.description: Number of threads cached in the thread cache. Will be zero if the thread pool is in use (see Thread pool in MariaDB 5.5).

item.name: MySQL ThreadPool connected threads
item.description: Number of open connections.

item.name: MySQL ThreadPool created threads
item.description: Number of threads created to respond to client connections. If too large, look at increasing thread_cache_size.

item.name: MySQL ThreadPool idle threads
item.description: Number of inactive threads in the thread pool. Only meaningful on Unixes, not tracked on Windows. Threads become idle either by waiting for new work, or if it's blocked due to disk io, row or table lock etc.

item.name: MySQL ThreadPool running threads
item.description: Number of threads that are actively running, not sleeping.

item.name: MySQL ThreadPool threads
item.description: Number of threads in the thread pool.

item.name: MySQL Triggers
item.description: Number of times triggers created with CREATE TRIGGER have executed. This differs from Com_create_trigger in that it is only incremented when the trigger has run, not when it executes.

item.name: MySQL Truncate commands
item.description: Number of TRUNCATE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Uninstall Plugin commands
item.description: Number of UNINSTALL PLUGIN commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Unlock Tables commands
item.description: Number of UNLOCK TABLES commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Update commands
item.description: Number of UPDATE commands executed.

item.name: MySQL Uptime
item.description: Number of seconds the server has been running.

item.name: MySQL Uptime since flush status
item.description: Number of seconds since the last FLUSH STATUS.

item.name: MySQL Waited table locks
item.description: Number of table locks which had to wait. Indicates table lock contention.

item.name: MySQL XA statements commited
item.description: Number of XA statements committed.

item.name: MySQL XA statements ended
item.description: Number of XA statements ended.

item.name: MySQL XA statements prepared
item.description: Number of XA statements prepared.

item.name: MySQL XA statements recover
item.description: Number of XA RECOVER statements executed.

item.name: MySQL XA statements rollback
item.description: Number of XA statements rolled back.

item.name: MySQL XA statements start
item.description: Number of XA statements started.

item.name: Zabbix script version
item.description: Provides version number of script running on host to monitor RabbitMQ. Should be same number as template user macro {$ZBX_TPL_VERSION}

item_prototype.name: Galera apply oooe
item_prototype.description: How often writesets have been applied out of order, an indicators of parallelization efficiency.

item_prototype.name: Galera apply oool
item_prototype.description: How often writesets with a higher sequence number were applied before ones with a lower sequence number, implying slow writesets.

item_prototype.name: Galera cert deps distance
item_prototype.description: Average distance between the highest and the lowest sequence numbers that can possibly be applied in parallel, or the potential degree of parallelization.

item_prototype.name: Galera cluster size
item_prototype.description: Number of nodes currently in the cluster

item_prototype.name: Galera flow control paused
item_prototype.description: Time since the most recent status query that was paused due to flow control

item_prototype.name: Galera flow control received
item_prototype.description: Number of FC_PAUSE events received as well as sent since the most recent status query.

item_prototype.name: Galera flow control sent
item_prototype.description: Number of FC_PAUSE events sent since the most recent status query

item_prototype.name: Galera last commited
item_prototype.description: Sequence number of the most recently committed transaction.

item_prototype.name: Galera local index
item_prototype.description: The node's index in the cluster. The index is zero-based.

item_prototype.name: Galera local receive queue
item_prototype.description: Current length of the receive queue, which is the number of writesets waiting to be applied.

item_prototype.name: Galera local send queue
item_prototype.description: Current length of the send queue, which is the number of writesets waiting to be sent.

item_prototype.name: Galera local transaction's certification failures per second
item_prototype.description: Total number of local transactions that failed the certification test.

item_prototype.name: Galera received writeset bytes per second
item_prototype.description: Total size in bytes of all writesets received from other nodes.

item_prototype.name: Galera received writesets per second
item_prototype.description: Total number of writesets received from other nodes.

item_prototype.name: Galera replicated writeset bytes per second
item_prototype.description: Total size in bytes of all writesets replicated to other nodes.

item_prototype.name: Galera replicated writesets per second
item_prototype.description: Total number of writesets replicated to other nodes.

item_prototype.name: Galera transaction's commits per second
item_prototype.description: Total number of local transactions committed on the node.

item_prototype.name: Galera transaction's replays per second
item_prototype.description: Total number of transaction replays due to asymmetric lock granularity.

item_prototype.name: Galera transactions aborted by slaves per second
item_prototype.description: Total number of local transactions aborted by slave transactions while being executed

trigger_prototype.name: Galera cluster is slowed down due to slave lag
Galera cluster size is different from expected
Galera node has too few slave threads
trigger_prototype.description: More transactions might be applied in parallel than configured in wsrep_slave_threads.

item_prototype.name: InnoDB available undo logs
item_prototype.description: Total number available InnoDB undo logs. Differs from MariaDB 10.0/MySQL 5.6's innoDB_undo_logs system variable, which specifies the number of active undo logs.

item_prototype.name: InnoDB background log sync
item_prototype.description: As shown in the BACKGROUND THREAD section of the SHOW ENGINE INNODB STATUS output.

item_prototype.name: InnoDB buffer pool data
item_prototype.description: Number of bytes contained in the InnoDB buffer pool, both dirty (modified) and clean (unmodified). See also Innodb_buffer_pool_pages_data, which can contain pages of different sizes in the case of compression.

item_prototype.name: InnoDB buffer pool dirty

item_prototype.name: InnoDB buffer pool wait free
item_prototype.description: Number of times InnoDB waited for a free page before reading or creating a page. Normally, writes to the InnoDB buffer pool happen in the background. When no clean pages are available, dirty pages are flushed first in order to free some up. This counts the numbers of wait for this operation to finish. If this value is not small, look at increasing innodb_buffer_pool_size.
